                <td colspan="2" width="18%" bgcolor="#400000"><font
                color="#FFFF80" size="2"
                face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica"><b>Epic Mobs Slain</b></font></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td colspan="2" bgcolor="#000000"><table
                border="0" cellpadding="3" cellspacing="0"
                width="100%">
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top" colspan="2" width="18%"
                        bgcolor="#000000"><img
                        src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/forum/icons/icon1.gif"
                        width="15" height="15"> <font
                        color="#FFFFCC" size="1"
                        face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">posted
                        by <strong><a href="kaelon@councilofarcana.com">Kaelon Xerxentis</a></strong> on
                        Friday, March 23, 2001 - 2:28 PM EST - <a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/cgi-forum/ubbmisc.cgi?action=sendthread&thread=http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/viewnews.cgi?newsid$newsid&Subject=Epic Mobs Slain"><img src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/envelope.gif" alt="E-mail Epic Mobs Slain" border=0></a> <a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/viewnews.cgi?newsid$newsid" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/printer.gif" alt="Print Epic Mobs Slain" border=0></a> </font><hr
                        size="1" color="#A8A8A8">
                        <font size="2"
                        face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Last night, the Council of Arcana engaged in a series of impromptu and strategic raids against epic mobs, epic bosses, and high level NPCs to assist a variety of its members with their Epic Quests. Significant encounters included Verina Tomb (level 60 Cleric from Neriak's Third Gate, for Sphyre's Enchanter Epic), The Tangrin (level 54 King Kong for Clarisse's Enchantress Epic), and we killed Captain Rottgrime not once, not twice, not even three times -- but four times for Fanielar (who organized the raid), Shalako, Lanenya, and Rabuf; and finally, General D`Veers -- the Level 60 Shadowknight leader of the Overthere Outpost -- sought to block our way, yet, he fell before our might. Congratulations, raiders -- let the battles continue! Please remember -- tonight we have <b><a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/fcouncilofarcanafrm1.showMessage?topicID=100.topic">this raid</a></b> at 8:00 pm Eastern, and this weekend, Ailen and Vandall will be leading <b><a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/fcouncilofarcanafrm1.showMessage?topicID=4.topic">this raid</a></b>, starting at 2:00 pm Eastern Time on Saturday from the South Ro Wizard Pyramid.</font>
                        <hr size="1" color="#A8A8A8">
                        <font size="2"
                        face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">


	<b><a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/talkback/985375694,93382,.shtml">Comments (0)</a></b>
	


</font>
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
                </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
        </td>
