<a name="newsitem984033281,93315,"></a>
<p>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="1" width="90%">
    <tr>
        <td bgcolor="#A8A8A8"><table border="0" cellpadding="4"
        cellspacing="1" width="100%">
            <tr>
                <td colspan="2" width="18%" bgcolor="#400000"><font
                color="#FFFF80" size="2"
                face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica"><b>Nagafen Defeated... Again</b></font></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td colspan="2" bgcolor="#000000"><table
                border="0" cellpadding="3" cellspacing="0"
                width="100%">
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top" colspan="2" width="18%"
                        bgcolor="#000000"><img
                        src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/forum/icons/icon1.gif"
                        width="15" height="15"> <font
                        color="#FFFFCC" size="1"
                        face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">posted
                        by <strong><a href="kaelon@councilofarcana.com">Kaelon Xerxentis</a></strong> on
                        Thursday, March 8, 2001 - 1:34 AM EST - <a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/cgi-forum/ubbmisc.cgi?action=sendthread&thread=http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/viewnews.cgi?newsid$newsid&Subject=Nagafen Defeated... Again"><img src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/envelope.gif" alt="E-mail Nagafen Defeated... Again" border=0></a> <a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/viewnews.cgi?newsid$newsid" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/printer.gif" alt="Print Nagafen Defeated... Again" border=0></a> </font><hr
                        size="1" color="#A8A8A8">
                        <font size="2"
                        face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">The Council of Arcana defeated Lord Nagafen in an impromptu raid on Tuesday, March 6th, 2001. The raid was led by Derxus and Sphyre/Liinks, and was a smashing success wherein Council members displayed their dedication to family and their commitment to the principles of selflessness and charity unparalleled. This serves as just another example of how we can channel our energies at a given moment's notice - and should serve as inspiration for future impromptu and spontaneous adventures. Congratulations, Dragon Slayers! (You can <b><a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/fcouncilofarcanafrm2.showMessage?topicID=76.topic">join in congratulating the raiders</a></b> at the link specified.)</font>
                        <hr size="1" color="#A8A8A8">
                        <font size="2"
                        face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">


	<b><a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/talkback/984033281,93315,.shtml">Comments (0)</a></b>
	


</font>
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
                </td>
            </tr>
