            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td colspan="2" bgcolor="#000000"><table
                border="0" cellpadding="3" cellspacing="0"
                width="100%">
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top" colspan="2" width="18%"
                        bgcolor="#000000"><img
                        src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/forum/icons/icon1.gif"
                        width="15" height="15"> <font
                        color="#FFFFCC" size="1"
                        face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">posted
                        by <strong><a href="kaelon@councilofarcana.com">Kaelon Xerxentis</a></strong> on
                        Tuesday, February 27, 2001 - 2:37 AM EST - <a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/cgi-forum/ubbmisc.cgi?action=sendthread&thread=http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/viewnews.cgi?newsid$newsid&Subject=Council Ledger Implemented"><img src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/envelope.gif" alt="E-mail Council Ledger Implemented" border=0></a> <a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/viewnews.cgi?newsid$newsid" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/printer.gif" alt="Print Council Ledger Implemented" border=0></a> </font><hr
                        size="1" color="#A8A8A8">
                        <font size="2"
                        face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">So, what does a Level 52 Wizard do when he can't log into EverQuest because of horrendous packet loss? Yup, you heard right - he becomes a Web Wizard and indulges in a project. I'm pleased to say that I've finally implemented a <b><a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/ledger.html">Council Ledger</a></b> that we can be proud to use and regularly visit. The Council Ledger supports file updates, unlimited character details and information, character avatars, and password protected accounts. Check it out, and be sure to add your character and keep your materials up to date. (Note: You should list your secondary/alternate characters in your "additional information" field.) In order for your character to display a proper rank, you will have to know the rank password. These passwords have been posted in the proper forums, so that only those who qualify to use the rank will know the password (check out the forums, thus, for details). Special thanks to the Guardian Brotherhood and Guardian Lords, both of Povar, for their creative inspiration and development expertise in helping this Arch Chancellor do his job.</font>
                        <hr size="1" color="#A8A8A8">
                        <font size="2"
                        face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">




</font>
