                        Sunday, January 7, 2001 - 2:09 PM EST - <a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/cgi-forum/ubbmisc.cgi?action=sendthread&thread=http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/viewnews.cgi?newsid$newsid&Subject=King Kong Raiding and more!"><img src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/envelope.gif" alt="E-mail King Kong Raiding and more!" border=0></a> <a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/viewnews.cgi?newsid$newsid" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/printer.gif" alt="Print King Kong Raiding and more!" border=0></a> </font><hr
                        size="1" color="#A8A8A8">
                        <font size="2"
                        face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">On Saturday night, the Council of Arcana successfully killed Tangrin "King Kong" in the Field of bone.  I wanted to quickly say that I was very proud of the high attendance and the wonderful job that everyone did!!  Thank you everyone to this wonderful job!!<br><br>After this event at Laer's suggesting, we headed to WK (after a few stops).  There we helped Clarisse get a white piece of paper, an enchanter epic quest item. After that we all headed to KC to help get wizard's their soul for the Brain Bite Quest.  Congrats to everyone!!  Pictures shall be posted soon!<br><br>Also a quick congrats to Laer on his successful planning of the first part of his Epic Raiding with a final big battle coming soon!!<br><br>People who where at the King Kong Raid include: Aluasa, Dindayen, Laer, Tezrian, Krawkowl, Winor, Niost, Jahve, Kirastar, Deadpoet, Mahogani, Heilig, Aulnde, Arboth, Corae, Belcoed, Sorren, and myself.</font>
