            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td colspan="2" bgcolor="#000000"><table
                border="0" cellpadding="3" cellspacing="0"
                width="100%">
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top" colspan="2" width="18%"
                        bgcolor="#000000"><img
                        src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/forum/icons/icon1.gif"
                        width="15" height="15"> <font
                        color="#FFFFCC" size="1"
                        face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">posted
                        by <strong><a href="kaelon@councilofarcana.com">Kaelon Xerxentis</a></strong> on
                        Wednesday, December 27, 2000 - 6:02 AM EST - <a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/cgi-forum/ubbmisc.cgi?action=sendthread&thread=http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/viewnews.cgi?newsid$newsid&Subject=Retroactive Mentorships Announced"><img src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/envelope.gif" alt="E-mail Retroactive Mentorships Announced" border=0></a> <a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/viewnews.cgi?newsid$newsid" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/printer.gif" alt="Print Retroactive Mentorships Announced" border=0></a> </font><hr
                        size="1" color="#A8A8A8">
                        <font size="2"
                        face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">The Arch Chancellor (that's me) announced today that the Office of the Arch Chancellory will be accepting special appeals for <b><a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/fcouncilofarcanafrm6.showMessage?topicID=9.topic">Retroactive Mentorships</a></b>. Under this policy, Junior Councilors who have been in the guild for at least 30 days and have not yet completed their mentorships, may send in a petition to the Arch Chancellor and have their mentorship periods waived, pending consideration. It is intended as tenative relief to those who have been unable to acquire mentors amidst the busy Holiday Season. The Retroactive Mentorship policy requires that you submit an essay and check-in. It is consistent with the values and ideals espoused by the Council of Arcana's Mentorship Program which has since been undergoing reformation. Full details can be found <b><a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/fcouncilofarcanafrm6.showMessage?topicID=9.topic">here</a></b>.</font>
                        <hr size="1" color="#A8A8A8">
                        <font size="2"
                        face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">




</font>
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
                </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
        </td>
    </tr>
