                        Friday, May 5, 2000 - 12:16 PM EDT - <a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/cgi-forum/ubbmisc.cgi?action=sendthread&thread=http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/viewnews.cgi?newsid$newsid&Subject=Structure, Power Changes in Address"><img src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/envelope.gif" alt="E-mail Structure, Power Changes in Address" border=0></a> <a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/viewnews.cgi?newsid$newsid" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/printer.gif" alt="Print Structure, Power Changes in Address" border=0></a> </font><hr
                        size="1" color="#A8A8A8">
                        <font size="2"
                        face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Arch Chancellor Kaelon Xerxentis issued his <b><a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/forum/Forum1/HTML/000203.html">Condition of the Council Address</a></b> today over the Council Chambers, because a majority of members were unable to attend tonight's speech in the Lake Rathe Arena (it is henceforth cancelled). In it, he has announced the creation of two new positions and indicated substantial changes in power structures, but has reaffirmed the foundation and basis of the Council as a community of friendship and comradery. The Membership Reform Act of 3184, was also called for acclamation. For more, please <b><a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/forum/Forum1/HTML/000203.html">read the address</a></b>.</font>
