                        by <strong><a href="kaelon@councilofarcana.com">Kaelon Xerxentis</a></strong> on
                        Wednesday, April 26, 2000 - 12:16 PM EDT - <a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/cgi-forum/ubbmisc.cgi?action=sendthread&thread=http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/viewnews.cgi?newsid$newsid&Subject=Membership Reform Act Proposed!"><img src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/envelope.gif" alt="E-mail Membership Reform Act Proposed!" border=0></a> <a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/viewnews.cgi?newsid$newsid" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/printer.gif" alt="Print Membership Reform Act Proposed!" border=0></a> </font><hr
                        size="1" color="#A8A8A8">
                        <font size="2"
                        face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Arch Chancellor Kaelon Xerxentis and High Councilor Luciano Manente have finished their work of many days and nights in creating and formulating the <b><a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/forum/Forum4/HTML/000042.html">Membership Reform Act of 3184</a></b>, an extensive document that calls for uniform membership admission, re-admission, and education/initial-promotion procedural policies and practices for the Council of Arcana. The High Council and the entire guild (via the Committee on Membership) are now engaged in discussions and amendments. Voting is scheduled for later this week. Please enjoy this excellent work.</font>
                        <hr size="1" color="#A8A8A8">
