                        Wednesday, April 19, 2000 - 11:27 PM EDT - <a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/cgi-forum/ubbmisc.cgi?action=sendthread&thread=http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/viewnews.cgi?newsid$newsid&Subject=Membership Admissions Policy Revised"><img src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/envelope.gif" alt="E-mail Membership Admissions Policy Revised" border=0></a> <a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/viewnews.cgi?newsid$newsid" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/printer.gif" alt="Print Membership Admissions Policy Revised" border=0></a> </font><hr
                        size="1" color="#A8A8A8">
                        <font size="2"
                        face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">In moving the guild closer to a Mentorship Program, Arch Chancellor Kaelon Xerxentis took the unusual step of issuing an edict in the Committee on Membership this evening calling for <b><a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/forum/Forum4/HTML/000038.html">new membership admissions requirements</a></b> to begin being enforced on all future received applications for membership. This decree follows the Council's deliberations on a new <b><a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/forum/Forum4/HTML/000036.html">Junior Councilor Mentorship program</a></b>, and the Arch Chancellor's imposition of a moratorium on all future promotions from Junior Councilor to full Councilor until such a new mentorship program is in place. Among the various new requirements, all applications must receive at least five yea votes, be supported by the sponsor, and be reviewed for no more than ten days from inception.</font>
                        <hr size="1" color="#A8A8A8">
                        <font size="2"
                        face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">




</font>
