                        Wednesday, April 19, 2000 - 9:27 AM EDT - <a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/cgi-forum/ubbmisc.cgi?action=sendthread&thread=http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/viewnews.cgi?newsid$newsid&Subject=Moratorium on JC Promotions Proclaimed"><img src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/envelope.gif" alt="E-mail Moratorium on JC Promotions Proclaimed" border=0></a> <a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/viewnews.cgi?newsid$newsid" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/printer.gif" alt="Print Moratorium on JC Promotions Proclaimed" border=0></a> </font><hr
                        size="1" color="#A8A8A8">
                        <font size="2"
                        face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Arch Chancellor Kaelon Xerxentis announced today in response to the Committee on Membership's Mentoring Program brainstorming session, that there be a new moratorium on promotions from Junior Councilor to Councilor -- meaning that newly admitted members will not be promoted to permanent members -- until the High Council and the Membership Committee come up with a new Junior Councilor and Mentorship Program. All are encouraged to <b><a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/forum/Forum4/HTML/000036.html">participate in this new social initiative</a></b> for our guild.</font>
