                        face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">posted
                        by <strong><a href="kaelon@alleria.com">Kaelon Xerxentis</a></strong> on
                        Friday, March 10, 2000 - 9:41 PM EST - <a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/cgi-forum/ubbmisc.cgi?action=sendthread&thread=http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/viewnews.cgi?newsid$newsid&Subject=Cerfnet Router Down"><img src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/envelope.gif" alt="E-mail Cerfnet Router Down" border=0></a> <a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/viewnews.cgi?newsid$newsid" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/printer.gif" alt="Print Cerfnet Router Down" border=0></a> </font><hr
                        size="1" color="#A8A8A8">
                        <font size="2"
                        face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Verant has reported via EverQuest that a Cerfnet router in Los Angeles is damaged/down and there is no ETA on its repair, although Cerfnet is looking into the problem. Many people (around 70 percent) cannot access the login/chat server, and those that can are reporting very high levels of network latency and major packet loss (as I just found out when I logged on myself). Let's pray for a quick recovery, but in the meantime, play with your Council friends on the <b><a href="cgi-forum/Ultimate.cgi">message boards</a></b>.</font>
                        <hr size="1" color="#A8A8A8">
