            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td colspan="2" bgcolor="#000000"><table
                border="0" cellpadding="3" cellspacing="0"
                width="100%">
                    <tr>
                        <td valign="top" colspan="2" width="18%"
                        bgcolor="#000000"><img
                        src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/forum/icons/icon1.gif"
                        width="15" height="15"> <font
                        color="#FFFFCC" size="1"
                        face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">posted
                        by <strong><a href="kaelon@alleria.com">Kaelon Xerxentis</a></strong> on
                        Thursday, March 2, 2000 - 10:24 PM EST - <a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/cgi-forum/ubbmisc.cgi?action=sendthread&thread=http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/viewnews.cgi?newsid$newsid&Subject=Membership Process Changed"><img src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/envelope.gif" alt="E-mail Membership Process Changed" border=0></a> <a href="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/viewnews.cgi?newsid$newsid" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.councilofarcana.com/news/printer.gif" alt="Print Membership Process Changed" border=0></a> </font><hr
                        size="1" color="#A8A8A8">
                        <font size="2"
                        face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Please be aware that the High Council and I have implemented a new system of admitting membership which remains consistent with the Council of Arcana's priority of selectivity, exclusivity and family-oriented community. From now all, all deliberations for new members will occur publicly over our <b><a href="cgi-forum/Ultimate.cgi">Council Chambers</a></b> and all potential members must, in addition to being sponsored, submit a detailed <b><a href="app.html">Membership Application</a></b> to be considered. All officers are instructed to observe this new procedure and direct interested candidates to the membership form before guilding. This is an order from the Arch Chancellor.</font>
                        <hr size="1" color="#A8A8A8">
                        <font size="2"
                        face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">




